Don Payne is a professional rodeo contestant known for his success in steer wrestling. Born and raised in Stephenville, Texas, Payne has made a name for himself in the rodeo world, earning over $126,000 in career earnings. In 2023, he made his debut at the National Finals Rodeo (NFR), showcasing his skills and determination in the sport.

Here you can follow Don Payne’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Don Payne

Don Payne grew up in a family with a strong rodeo background, which influenced his passion for the sport. He began competing in rodeo events at a young age and quickly developed a talent for steer wrestling. 

As he progressed in his career, Payne gained recognition for his impressive performances and dedication to the sport.

Payne’s success in rodeo can be attributed to his hard work, determination, and natural talent. He has consistently demonstrated his ability to excel in high-pressure situations, making him a formidable competitor in the world of professional rodeo.

Early Career

In his early career, Don Payne focused on honing his skills in steer wrestling and building a reputation as a promising young talent. 

He participated in various rodeo events, gaining valuable experience and learning from seasoned competitors.

Professional Career

Don Payne’s professional career has been marked by numerous achievements and accolades. In 2023, he qualified for his debut National Finals Rodeo (NFR) in the 15th position.

Some of his major wins include the Henderson County Rodeo, the Reno Rodeo, the Greeley Stampede, and the Dodge City Round-Up. He has also won the Gooding Pro Rodeo with a 3.6-second run, which helped him secure the 13th position in the World Standings.

Throughout his career, Payne has consistently demonstrated his ability to excel in high-pressure situations, making him a formidable competitor in the world of professional rodeo.

Don Payne’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Don Payne’s estimated net worth is $800k.

However, his career earnings amount to over $126,000, which has likely contributed significantly to his overall net worth.

Career Earnings

Throughout his career, Don Payne has earned a significant amount in prize money from various rodeo events. As of 2023, his career earnings amount to $126,592.

Some of his notable earnings include a win at the Gooding Pro Rodeo, where he picked up a check for $3,760.

His consistent success in steer wrestling has allowed him to accumulate substantial earnings and establish himself as a top competitor in the sport.

Personal Details

Wife

Don Payne is married to a woman named Shaina. Shaina’s father played a significant role in Don’s career, helping him learn the basics of steer wrestling.

Together, Don and Shaina have a son, and as of 2023, they are expecting their second child.

How Old is Don Payne?

Don Payne is 29 years old.

How tall is he?

He is 6 ft 4 in.

What is his nationality?

He is an American.

FAQs About Don Payne

When did he make his debut at the National Finals Rodeo (NFR)?

He made his debut at the National Finals Rodeo in 2023.

What is his net worth?

As of 2023, his net worth is $800k.

Who is his wife?

He married Shaina.
